<item>
            <title>[LU-1289] Fix Linux module version</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1289</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The module version string printed by Lustre modules is completely useless, usually something like &quot;0.1.0&quot; or similar.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Use the LUSTRE_VERSION_STRING to set the module version to the current Lustre version.  This is OK for the Lustre modules, but some work is needed to get a version string for libcfs/lnet modules, because they should technically not use any code from lustre/.  Probably moving the LUSTRE_VERSION_STRING definition into libcfs would be easiest.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
